Batelco, Qatar Islamic Bank, Sabic, Zain: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-03-14T05:27:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/bahrain-telecommunications-sabic-zain-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.    Saudi Arabia ’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 0.2 percent
and the Dubai Financial Market General Index rose 4.3 percent.       Bahrain Telecommunications Co. (BATELCO BI): The phone
company known as Batelco expects a decline of between 17 percent
and 20 percent in net profit in 2011, Chief Executive Officer
Peter George Kaliaropoulos said. The shares dropped 1.4 percent
to 0.414 dinar when they last traded March 10.    Kingdom Holding Co. (KINGDOM)  : The company controlled by
Saudi billionaire Prince Alwaleed bin Talal and Bahrain
Telecommunications Co. (BATELCO BI) offered $950 million to
purchase Mobile Telecommunications Co.’s (ZAIN KK) 25 percent
stake in Zain Saudi Arabia (ZAINKSA AB). Mobile
Telecommunications surged 4.4 percent to 1,420 fils in  Kuwait 
and Zain Saudi Arabia soared 9.2 percent to 7.15 riyals. Kingdom
advanced 6.9 percent to 9.3 riyals.       Qatar Islamic Bank (QIBK)  : The Persian Gulf country’s
biggest Islamic lender wants to enter the Turkish market and is
looking into buying the shariah-compliant units of other lenders
in  Qatar , its acting Chief Executive Officer Ahmad Meshari said
in Doha yesterday. The shares were unchanged at 79.2 riyals.        Saudi Basic Industries Corp. (SABIC)  : HSBC Holdings Plc
said it provided $435 million in long-term financing to Hadeed,
a unit of the world’s biggest petrochemicals maker, to build a
steel plant and rolling mill in Jubail in Saudi Arabia’s eastern
province. The shares fell 1 percent to 101.5 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  